quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  16,88,"Those who denied and barred from the way of Allah—We{1}added punishment to their punishment on account of the corruption they used to cause.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 3rd  person to 1st person.
  16,89,"And on a day when We raise in every community a witness against them from among them, and We brought<a class=""sup""><sup>c </sup></a>you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>as a witness against these. For We have bestowed upon you the Scripture from on high, as an explanation of everything and guidance and mercy and glad tidings for the Muslims{1}.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Muslimeenwhich means those who willingly submit to God, regardless of which prophet they followed.
  16,90,"Indeed, Allah commands to justice and excelling in doing good and bringing{1}<i class=""s"">(charity) </i>to the relative, and He forbids obscenity and what is deplorable and oppression. He admonishes you, that you may <span class=""h"">remind yourselves<sup foot_note=""80406"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>.",footnotes:1:The Qur’an always uses verb ‘to bring’ rather than verb ‘to give’ in association with charity; this should be pondered by the reader.
  16,91,"And fulfill<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>Allah’s covenant when you make a covenant, and do not violate your oaths after ratifying them, for surely you have made Allah your guarantor; indeed, Allah knows what you do."
  16,92,"And do<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>not be like she who unravels her yarn, breaking it into pieces after she has spun it strongly, by using your oaths as a means of deception among you because one community is more prosperous than another community. Indeed, Allah is testing you thereby, and He will most surely clarify to you on the Day of Resurrection whatever you used to differ over."
  16,93,"And had Allah willed, He would have made you one community, but He leads astray whom He wills, and He guides whom He wills, and you will most surely be asked about what you used to do."
